{"by":"jedberg","id":47773872,"kids":[47773952,47778398,47774187,47774177,47774596,47774405,47774019,47776880],"parent":47772012,"text":"We need a law that says if you hold any data about a person, they <i>must</i> be notified when anyone accesses it, including law enforcement.<p>I used to work in criminal investigations.  I understand how this might make investigation of real crime more difficult.  But so does the fact that you need a warrant to enter someone&#x27;s home, and yet we manage to investigate crime anyway.<p>Your data should be an extension of your home, even if it&#x27;s held by another company.  It should require a warrant <i>and</i> notification.  You could even make the notification be 24 hours after the fact.  But it should be required.","time":1776219284,"type":"comment"}